      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism is a judicial philosophy that holds the Constitution should be interpreted based on the original understanding of its text at the time it was adopted. Proponents of this view argue that the Founders' intent provides the only legitimate basis for constitutional meaning, preventing judges from imposing their own modern policy preferences. This approach is used to maintain the rule of law by ensuring that the Constitution's meaning remains fixed rather than evolving with current social trends.",
